      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a decent start for a general overview, but it's a bit surface-level for a high school policy debate tier. they need more philosophical depth. can you expand on the \"national sovereignty\" part? like, how do proponents link the physical boundary specifically to the legitimacy of the state itself? and maybe include some arguments regarding the economic impact on domestic labor markets from the perspective of those favoring stricter enforcement. give me the strongest version of those points.",
