      "content": "The concept of national sovereignty is fundamentally tied to the state's exclusive right to govern its territory, making a physical border the ultimate expression of that authority. Without rigorously enforced borders, a nation's jurisdiction becomes porous, undermining the very legal framework that defines the state. Economically, strict enforcement is argued to protect domestic wage earners by limiting the supply of low-skilled labor, thereby preventing downward pressure on wages for American workers. This structured approach ensures that economic growth benefits citizens who adhere to the established legal and fiscal obligations of the nation.",
